<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1167835321583"><term>annuity</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1167835321588">An annuity is an investment that is a sequence of equal periodic deposits.</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167835468374"><term>common ratio</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1167835468378">The ratio between consecutive terms in a geometric sequence, <m:math><m:mrow><m:mfrac><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>a</m:mi><m:mi>n</m:mi></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>a</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow></m:mfrac><m:mo>,</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> is <emphasis effect="italics">r</emphasis>, the common ratio, where <emphasis effect="italics">n</emphasis> is greater than or equal to two.</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167835468417"><term>geometric sequence</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1167835468421">A geometric sequence is a sequence where the ratio between consecutive terms is always the same</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167835468427"><term>infinite geometric series</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1167835468431">An infinite geometric series is an infinite sum infinite geometric sequence.</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
